> <OLD - Nightlight>
>
> Nighlight was torn in two, she didnt like to leave Rodimus behind but she
> didnt like to be close of Magmatron and Saberback. She finally answer "How
> did you find me? I... i cannot contact any body. Some thing is blocking my
> comlink... Besides... I cannot leave my husband behind... Its Rodimus... He
> has changed so much, its almost as if he were other person"
>
> All the tension, the fear and harsh conditions that she was endured all that
> time was taking the toll on her phisically and mentally.

<NEW>

LONGRACK shook his head, "We don't have time for all of this." His
face looked nervous as if he half expected SHARKTICON troopers to
burst in any moment. "I hacked Magmataron's own com-link system. It
seems to work, at least here in his base."

"But we lost Tuscon." This said by a black and brown MAXIMAL who
looked as if he turned into some sort of cobra-like snake. "And we
don't know where Rodimus is."

LONGRACK gestured for quiet as he went to the door. "Come on." He said
after a short look outside. "The coast is still clear, we've got to
go, now!"

The MAXIMALS began to walk out the door, falling into a quick jog.
"Come on." LONGRACK said as he to NIGHTSHIFT, he was the last to
leave.
